Lists all modules available to be loaded

Source: R/high_level.R
module_avail.Rd

Lists all modules available to be loaded

Usage

module_avail(starts_with = NULL, contains = NULL)

Arguments

starts_with

An optional character scalar. If provided, only modules whose name starts with this character string will be returned.

contains

An optional character scalar. This parameter is only supported in Environment Modules 4.3+. If provided, it will filter modules to only those containing this substring.

Value

A character vector with class "cli_ansi_string".

Examples

module_avail()
